Description: A conical jar-seal: of brown clay with a red pottery lid adhering to the underside. The seal bears four impressed inscriptions, one of which is not very visible.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' II, pl.XIII, 91; H. R. Hall, 'Catalogue of Egyptian scarabs etc. in the British Museum: Volume 1 : Royal scarabs' (London, 1913), 286, no.2 750; P. Kaplony, 'Die Inschriften der Ägyptischen Frühzeit III (Wiesbaden, 1963), pl.9, abb.26A; see also vol. I, 60 and II, 686, n.44; 718 n.181; 1094.
